A story gets interesting only when therez a twist. So pls expect a small twist in the tale 😀 

Concept and DOP - @rakshitha.nrk @streetlightbyrakshitha
Edit - @ramanis2udio_official
Saree - @varnamgallery
Our barbie : @swatsiv
Jewellery - @tashaprem_collections
MUAH - @rz_sareedrapist
Blouse - @bollyfashion_tailoring @zara

Saree is something that's not just cherished only  by Indian girls,it's loved across the globe, so this time around let's drape it on our own barbie ❤️

Saree - by varnam gallery - you have to wear it to believe how comfortable and easy it is to have it as your second skin (the mul series collections).You can see it for yourself here. Can drape it in any style.

Jewellery - Tashaprem collections
Visit their store for enormous collections. We wanted something not heavy in weight and we had so many options to choose from and for this concept we went for  big German silver jhumka (trust me it wasn't heavy at all)  and guttapoosalu set. Stunning and elegant !

MUAH - Rana, a man of taste. He slightly changed the look for each concept and we just showed what style of saree drape that we needed and he draped within a few minutes. 

Blouse by Bolly fashions- we dint want the usual blouse and requested for a long sleeve. The material n pattern was spot on for us.

And needless to say that Swathi who lived the role of Barbie. And this is how Barbie would be as a human amidst us. Isn't it ? Barbie in reality 😀

I truly cherish the time we spent together for this concept. We all would be working more together going forward.

Cheers
StreetLightbyRakshitha
